		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    A better druids guide for levels 1-30 with details</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:">Asdion</a> | 
		            9/17/2001 3:48:06 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">So you want to be a druid?  We are the best class in the world tied with shamans.  We can kill giants at level 30 and im still working on it for a hell level and im almost passed it!  Well anyways,to start off you shuold put all of the points you can into Wisdom cause that will be your main mana pool from level 1 to 60.  Place the other 5 in stamina is what i did cause i have about 800hp at level 30.  I like playing a wood elf druid but i guess any type will do i mean a druid is a druid.  If you choose woodelf, you start off in kelethin right in front of the druid guild.  Turn your note in for your tunic.  I think you shouldn't beg this early in the game. but you can if you want to.  Head to the newbie grounds after scribing your spells.  I never used burst of flame since its just a waste to me.  Evocation goes up fast though.  Stay in the newbie area with your club.  If you find a rusty scimitar or worn great staff, use those sell ANY cracked staves you find cause of their values.  1 platinum piece each staff and get a skill in tailoring or find one in the zone and get some Patch Work armor cause you'll need it for orcs.  just hunt the wolfs and wasps and bats on newbie grounds.  This will get you to level 2.  At level 2, just hunt orc pawns and maybe a pixie or two.  Basically kill anything you see on newbie grounds.  By this time you should have the spell snare.  Use it cause that is one of the druids most powerful spell.  instead of the enemy still attacking while rooted and hes about to die, snare makes it so he doesnt fight back and hes rooted.  Just hunt everything on newbie grounds til level 5.  Thats what i did.  After reaching level 5 i prefer to head over to the butcherblok mountains after getting your spells.  Definately get burst of fire does 15 damage and the wind spell.  the wind spell will do 22 points of damage.  Once in butcherblok, find the trail in front of the entrance to greater faydark.  just follow the path and dont worry about the goblins or if you are get the camoflauge spell for invisibility.  When following the path, you'll see a place with 2 houses one on the left and right of the trail keep following the path.  You'll meet at a crossroad. next to it is a house wiht guards in it they will be your best friend til level 8.  Just hunt around the guard hut and dont kill any skeletons or giant scarabs around there cause they will murder you.  This should get you to level 6 fast and no one is there so its all for you!  at level 6, your corpses will take a full real time day to decay or vanish.  Just stay here til you reach level 8 and hunt anything that is black or blue to you.  Once you reach level 8,  Head back to your druids guild in kelethin and get the skill meditate.  it increases your mana regrowth.  Head back to butcherblok and stayy there til level 9.  Once level 9, try to get a teleport from another druid or wizard and go to Western Commons.  Get your spells first of course cause you get a 37 damage spell.  Once at western commons, go to the druid ruins if not already there. This will be your main hunting grounds for now until level 14!<BR>
loot is nice as well bears drop pelts worth 30 platinum pieces.  Just stay here til level 14 as i said.  Once level 14,  Go to freeport and buy the spell BIND AFFINITY.  Once you buy and scribe it, bind yourself to the freeport area and get another portal to greater faydark from a friendly wizard or druid and get directions to there from Butcherblok.  Once your at you druid guild, get the spells Spirit of Wolf, Stinging Swarm, Skin like Rock, and the others if you wish.  After buying the spells get gate if you dont already have it and scribe that and cast it.  You will be back in freeport.  From there get someone to guide you to The Oasis of Marr.  once there watch out for the skeletons there and sand giants(hits fr 94 damage) and spectres.  Get a group or use grasping roots (level 5 root spell) and cast Stinging Swarm.  It will do 117 points of damage in a minute.  Snare it then cast ignite until its dead once the stinging swarm wears off.  Just keep doing this until some crocs are green to you and thta will be around level 18 i think. From there, you can kill the skeletons and deepwater crocodiles.  Just use the root, stinging swamr, snare and ignite skill and you can hit level 19 and your new spells in no time at all.  From there go to the freeport bank and get some money out or all you have and head back to the Western commons druid ring and there is a merchant the with the lastname of pinewhisper i think it is but im not sure and buy your Teleport spells.  ONLY the rings of butcher, karana, commons, and toxxulia.  Scribe them and cast ring of butcher.  You will end up in butcherblok and head back to the kelethin guild and get soem of your spells like dizzying wind, and careless lightning.  Awesome spells high damage.well once you get all your necesary spells, your gonna make a long journey to the lands of Kunark. Head over to the docks and from facing the water follow the left wall and you will come across a dock with 4 platforms.  Take the one farthest to your upper left hand side.  You will head to a big ship after zoning into the timorous deep.  Head on the ship and onvce you go up the platform, stay at the deck in ship until you zone again.  And you will wind up in firiona vie.  You shoukld bind once you get off.  You'll know when your there.  If you dont have the spell superior camoflauge, head to Norht karana i tihnk it is and get it.  Then get someone to guide you to the lake of Ill omen.  Make that person take you to the &quot;Windmills&quot;.  Bind yourself inside of the mill.  a merchant is in there so no need to head to firiona again unless your banking.  stay here til level 25 or 26.  Hunt the TIGERS not TIGERESSES.  Kill the sarnak courier if you get him on track.  Oh yeahh once level 20, you can get a last name and get the skill TRACK.  hunt goblin battlemasters and sarnak flunkies til level 25.  Once your level 25, head over to North Karana and get your new spells like wolfform and creeping crud(210 dmg spell.  Upgrade to stinging swarm but dont cast both on target just cast creeping crud.  You also get new spell effects you'll notice.  Once you get your spells, head to the stone bridge from the druids by heading South West form druid ring and follow the shore to the right once you hit it.  You'll see the stone bridge and go through it and you'll zone into South karana. Bind at the bridge on south karana side.  Then get someone to guide you to the Spires with gnolls. You cant solo these YET. just group them they drop Fine steel weapons and about 5pp and other various awesome items. If you pick up the gloves, equip them cause they give more wisdom.  But by now you should have some awesome items thta give wisdom. Get ANY items that give wisdom and you should give up meleeing by now.  Tanks will do your work for ya.  Just stay grouped til level 28 and then you Solo the gnolls but get a spire thats not camped.  That place is popular but if your going for cyclops's, group them and pull and named NPC's except the brother peop[le like qwinn and maybe pull Quillmane but some people pay 5kpp for the clock she dropds. Its for mage epic so dont loot it unless anyones looking for it.  Its no drop so dont pick it up unless you roll for it.  Watch out for the sentries and others.  Pull anything except those 4 people i told you about cause they are uber. Just stay around here til level 29.  Then you will head to steamfont mountains for your new 171 damage spell and you get another damage spell like creeping crud except you can cast both of them on one creature so your doing about 500 dmg with immolate and creeping crud.  Now you can solo with ease to creatures your level. once your spells are ready, Head to butcherblok and kill the crazed goblins.  They should be as high as 30.  Awesome experience so stay there until level 30 and then what i have been doing is hunting sand giants and griffins in Western commons for experience they are easy if root and DoT's stick<BR>
ALWAYS USE SNARE.  Always use snare til level 29 then you get one that lasts for 10 minutes!  only if it sticks of course. well i hope my guide will help many on their quest to power and fortune.  One more thing to add is that experience will go slowly at level 30 and DONT HUNT THE SAND GIANTS IN OASIS.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Asdion Moonmagic (GM picked last name for me so i feel blessed =P)<BR>
level 30 druid 1 and a half yellow away from 31 and out of a hell level!<BR>
Erolissi Marr server<BR>
Guild: Oracles of Fate ( join when possible =P )
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
