				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				#1 Use your burst of flame spell ASAP<BR>
#2 wood  elf or halling druids are the only way to go. If you want a human or half elf *shudder* you're going to have to make a huge sacrifice in wisdom.<BR>
#3 800 hit points at 30? I had 800 hit points at 44. 5 Stamina will do next to nothing to your hitpoints, which doesnt really matter because druids aren't tanks. Put it into strength. I tend to get encumbered a lot, and regret not doing so in the first place. It will be much more convenient.<BR>
#4 I tend to hunt in greater faydark from 1-14, due to the fact that there is orc hill from 4-9, and cb from 9-14. The crushbone belts sell well, and are fairly common. Besides that, you are always a stones-throw away from spells/a trainer.<BR>
<BR>
 1-5 usual newbie ground garbage<BR>
 6-8 orc hill<BR>
 9-14 crushbone<BR>
 14-18 Alluring sirens in OOT (easy to spot, jump off the BB-&gt;FP boat)<BR>
 18-20 Highhold pass<BR>
 21-32 Highhold keep<BR>
 32-44 Dwarves, Hill giants, Gnomes, Or eastern wastes wandering MOBs/Rygorr fort. This should give you a nice change of pace.<BR>
 45- several places on kunark, velious. If you dont have either of these expansions, getting to  50 wil be a bit difficult.<BR>
<BR>
   Thats all I have to say, thanks -- Raeneth<BR>
